        "text": "I think the first piece is that you absolutely need to have one, to start by saying that. Regardless of what level you are in the company. So people say, \"Oh, I'm just a junior PM.\" Whatever level, there is some micro macro vision that you need to have. Because essentially if you got on a plane and the pilot was like, \"I don't really know where we're going, but I'm a really good pilot. The company needs to fly 400 flights this year. So I'm trying to make that happen, but trust me, we'll get there. There might be turbulence, I'm not sure.\" You probably would be thinking twice about staying on that flight, right? What happens is you get on there, it's like, \"Our destination is Miami.\" Maybe I'm dreaming of beaches, \"And it's going to be 24 degrees when we get there.\" And he always paints or she paints this image of the destination."
